      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks but the scripts dont help with the actual math of it. like, if you look at the sheer amount of suffering vs the amount of actual joy, it feels like the system is broken. if you were an optimizer trying to solve for the least amount of suffering, wouldnt you just see that more life just means more more pain? how do you calculate the value of something that just creates more entropy?",
